<div type="translation" xml:lang="eng" source="bib:Srinivasan1964_01">
	<p>This home of Śiva named Śrī-śikhari-pallaveśvaram, was caused to be made at Siṃhapura <supplied reason="explanation">Ciṅkavaram</supplied> by king Candrāditya who was a <foreign>sarvanātha</foreign>.</p>
	<note>Translation by K.R. Srinivasan (1964). Standardised according to DHARMA TG and EG.</note><!--check-->
</div>
      	
<div type="translation" xml:lang="fre" resp="part:sybr">
	<p>Le roi Candrāditya, maître de l’univers, fit construire</p>
	<p>Cette demeure de Śiva, appelée Śrī-Śikhari-Pallaveśvara, à Siṅhapura.</p>
	
</div>

         <div type="commentary">
         	<p>Note on Śrī-Śikhari-Pallaveśvara.</p><!--update!-->
         	<p>Note on Siṃhapura  = Ciṅkavaram.</p><!--update!-->
         </div>

